data.chText: 他兼任作曲家和指挥的双重角色
data.enText: his dual role as composer and conductor
She has dual nationality (= is a citizen of two different countries) .

data.chText: 这件家具有两个用途，既作橱柜也作饭桌。
data.enText: The piece of furniture serves a dual purpose as a cupboard and as a table.

data.chText: 这两个形容词常与下列名词连用：
data.enText: These adjectives are frequently used with the following nouns.

data.chText: dual用于有两个部分、两种用途或两个方面的事物。
data.enText: Dual describes something that has two parts, uses or aspects.

data.chText: double具有相似的意思，但所描述事物的两个部分通常是相同或相似的。
data.enText: Double can be used with a similar meaning, but when it is used to describe something that has two parts, the two parts are usually the same or very similar.

data.chText: 指供给两人或两事物的东西或较平常大一倍的东西用double，不用dual。
data.enText: Double , but not dual , can describe something that is made for two people or things, or is twice as big as usual.

simple_means.memory_skill: du 二，双 + al …的 → 二重的；二元的

tr: a grammatical number category referring to two items or units as opposed to one item (singular) or more than two items (plural)
example: ancient Greek had the dual form but it has merged with the plural form in modern Greek

tr: consisting of or involving two parts or components usually in pairs
example: an egg with a double yolk
dual controls for pilot and copilot
duple (or double) time consists of two (or a multiple of two) beats to a measure

tr: having more than one decidedly dissimilar aspects or qualities
public preaching and private influence"- R.W.Emerson
example: a double (or dual) role for an actor
the office of a clergyman is twofol
every episode has its double and treble meaning"-Frederick Harriso

value.def: Dual means having two parts, functions, or aspects.

example.ex: ...his dual role as head of the party and head of state...
example.tran: 他作为政党领袖和国家元首的双重身份

example.ex: Rob may be entitled to dual nationality.
example.tran: 罗布或许能拥有双重国籍。
